      "content": "the \"quiet\" i'm talking about isn't like taking a nap or sitting in a park. it feels more like a permanent stop. like when a train reaches the very last station on the line and the engine just shuts off for good. i’m looking at these beautiful places and i just don't see the point in staying for the next leg of the trip. it feels like i've completed my journey and now i'm just... waiting to clock out. doesn't it seem logical to just finish when there's nothing left to see?",
